vulnerability_location.description: Unchecked addition of this.balance and msg.value in adr.transfer(this.balance + msg.value) can overflow in Solidity versions before 0.8.0
Low-level call adr.call.value(msg.value)(data) with unchecked return value

The multiplicate function uses a check `if(msg.value>=this.balance)` to trigger a payout of `this.balance + msg.value`. An attacker can observe a pending multiplicate call in the mempool and front-run it by submitting their own transaction with equal or higher value, draining the contract balance before the victim’s transaction executes.
Uses a floating pragma version (^0.4.18) which can introduce compiler inconsistencies, and performs a low-level call (adr.call.value(msg.value)(data)) without checking the return value
